&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-10775-2.2-dtest/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-10775-3.0-dtest/3/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-10775-trunk-dtest/lastCompletedBuild/testReport/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The only failing dtest related to compression is &lt;tt&gt;jmxmetrics_test.TestJMXMetrics.begin_test&lt;/tt&gt;. As explained in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10225&quot; title=&quot;Make compression ratio much more accurate&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10225&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10225&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the compression assertion is , in my opinion, just wrong. I removed it from the DTest. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15029818" author="blerer" created="Fri, 27 Nov 2015 12:21:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed into 2.2 at e7116f22cccdc91fa1d84e5e910af5c7a4393478 and merged into 3.0, 3.1 and trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
